                Caeciliae Birronis <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertae</ex></expan> Pyrallidi <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> Laelius <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertus</ex></expan> Donatus <lb n="4"/>et Caecilia Felicula et <lb n="5"/>Caecilia Faustilla <expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>ene</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erenti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecerunt</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/>in <expan><abbr>fr</abbr><ex>onte</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>edes</ex></expan> XII <lb n="7"/>in <expan><abbr>agr</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>edes</ex></expan> XII
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Buchstaben mit Ruß nachgezogen. (B): in fr(onte) in agr(o) p(edes) XII statt in fr(onte) p(edes) XII in agr(o) p(edes) XII. Sistrum auf Stein deutet wohl auf Verbindung der Genannten zum Isis-Kult hin.</p>
            </div>
